      • isValidValue

        protected boolean isValidValue(String valueStr)
        Returns true if the value matches the regular expression. If the pattern is not set this method always returns true. The entire String must match the pattern for the result to be true. Check if the value is valid, the isValueRequired property will have already been validated against an empty value. A null or empty string will never be passed to this method.
        Specified by:
        isValidValue in class StringValueValidator
        Parameters:
        valueStr - The value as returned by getComponentValue() .
        Returns:
        true if the component data is valid.

      • setPatternAsString

        public void setPatternAsString(String pattern)
        Set the regular expression pattern using a String. The Pattern.compile(java.lang.String) method is used to compile the pattern.
        Parameters:
        pattern - The pattern to set, if null the pattern will be null.
